Let me rephrase:

Having in the same app a situation where a DELETE causes a subsequent 
GET to return a 200 and a DELETE causing a subsequent GET returning a 
404 breaks the uniform constraint. Because we are talking about two 
different operations here, the first DELETE isn&#39;t really deleting a 
resource, it&#39;s modifying it&#39;s state, so it&#39;s more of a hack. But hacks 
happen, I use them lot&#39;s of time...

